{
  "stem": "3022.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, in 1943, when the SS came in and it became a concentration camp, before we were tattooed-- the Ukrainian guards came into the camp to build a barrack for the [GERMAN] and also a bond for his horses.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they bragged about this man and what a hero he was, that he single-handed-- supposedly-- he executed the town of Przemysl.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He killed single-handed about 600 people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then he gave his handgun to his six-year-old son to kill children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So when this man came in, we were rather concerned about his behavior.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And whatever reputation preceded him was justified.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He had a horse-- he had a dog by the name of Prince, who was trained to jump at your throat if you didn't take your hat off, or go for your testicles if you passed by with your hands in your pockets.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He also had two perfectly matching white horses.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And here's this man, who during the week, would come into the camp, kill people or sentence them to death, or beat them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then on Sunday, he would hitch the two horses, take his wife and take his son on a very leisurely Sunday drive.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He led a totally normal life, just outside the camp, which was in [GERMAN] I was in his apartment.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was awakened one morning when I was on the night shift, to come in and fix the toy that his boy had.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He had a tank that worked on a spring that he wound up.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the spring apparently broke.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I looked at it, and I said I have to take the tank into the shop to fix it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I was bending down, taking it apart, he kicked me in the behind.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he says, [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
